Project TacticaVirtualTabletop: 3D Virtual Tabletop

TacticaVirtualTabletop is a lightweight, high-performance Virtual Tabletop (VTT) environment designed for tabletop gaming and 3D visualization. Built with a Python-based Flask backend and a Three.js frontend, it features a sleek, "cutting-edge" sci-fi interface with real-time world synchronization.

🚀 Key Features

Dynamic 3D Environment: A full-screen 3D tabletop utilizing Three.js with support for STL models and PNG textures.

Blender-Style Manipulation: Integrated TransformControls allow for intuitive movement (World Space), rotation (Local Space), and scaling of objects directly in the browser.

Real-Time Polling Engine: A smart "diffing" system that monitors status.json and updates the 3D scene every $n$ milliseconds without unnecessary re-renders.

Integrated File Server: A custom file manager with a visual hierarchy tree for managing directories and uploading assets to the server.

Live JSON Configuration: Two dedicated editor modules to modify config.json (system settings) and status.json (world state) in a human-readable, pretty-printed format.

Sci-Fi Aesthetic: A "dark-mode" rectangular UI inspired by futuristic terminal interfaces.

Customizable Skybox: Support for immersive 360° backgrounds settable via the configuration panel.

🛠️ Tech StackBackend: 
Flask (Python)

Frontend 3D Engine: Three.js

3D Controls: OrbitControls (Camera) & TransformControls (Objects)

Styling: Custom CSS3 with Neon-Cyan accents

Data Storage: JSON-based state management

📂 Installation & Setup

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/Sinilaboratories/TacticaVirtualTabletop.git

cd TacticaVirtualTabletop

Install dependencies:

pip install Flask werkzeug

Run the terminal:

python app.py

Access the interface:
Navigate to http://localhost:5000 in your web browser.

🎮 Controls
Key     Action

Left Click  Select Object
W   Translate Mode (World Space)
E   Rotate Mode (Local Space)
R   Scale Mode (Local Space)
Esc Deselect ObjectMouse
WheelZoom   CameraRight
ClickOrbit  CameraSystem 

Note: Ensure all 3D assets are uploaded to the uploads/ directory via the File Manager to be accessible by the 3D engine.